core.conflict

Class DiscardConflictResolutionStrategy<T,E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • core.conflict.AbstractConflictResolutionStrategy<T,E>
      • core.conflict.DiscardConflictResolutionStrategy<T,E>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of entities that define the conflict scope of this conflict resolution strategy.
    E - The type of entities that underly the conflict incurred by the conflict source entity resolved by this conflict resolution strategy.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    IConflictResolutionStrategy<T,E>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DiscardConflictingAssociationConflictResolutionStrategy, DiscardConflictingAttributeConflictResolutionStrategy, DiscardConflictingDependencyConflictResolutionStrategy

    public class DiscardConflictResolutionStrategy<T,E>
extends AbstractConflictResolutionStrategy<T,E>
    a DiscardConflictResolutionStrategy generic class used to define a generic discarding conflict resolution strategy.

    This strategy consists of keeping the original elements of a conflict source entity, for a given conflict scope, while discarding the elements that gave rise to the conflict, as well as the changes incurred by them on the conflict domain's state. In this case, we consider that this behavior is justified by the fact that the original elements and the elements that gave rise to the conflict share the same semantics. Therefore, the conflict-spawning elements are copies of the original elements, and can be safely discarded.

    Author:
    Bachar Rima
